- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the Constraint Satisfaction Problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the Constraint Satisfaction Problem is a common problem in AI and the paper may have implications for AI applications. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper may have implications for geometric constraint satisfaction problems.
